Class Level

java.lang.Object
org.ziqi.model.Level
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<GameObject[]>
public final class Level
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<GameObject[]>
Level class represents a game level and contains all information for that game level.
Author:
Ziqi Yang-modified

  • Constructor Details

    • Level

      public Level​(java.lang.String levelName, int levelIndex, java.util.List<java.lang.String> raw_level)
      Level constructor initializes and stores the information of level from given parameters. This constructor is called when LevelManager is loading a new set of levels, all levels in that set will be generated respectively.
      Parameters:
      levelName - String value specifying the name of level.
      levelIndex - Integer specifying the index of the level.
      raw_level - List of strings as raw level lines read from resource file.
      See Also:
      refreshLevel(), LevelManager, LevelManager.loadSet(InputStream, String)

    • getGameObjectAt

      public GameObject getGameObjectAt​(int layer, java.awt.Point source)
      Gets the GameObject specified at the given position of the given layer.
      Parameters:
      layer - Integer specifying the layer index.
      source - Point object specifying the position of GameObject.
      Returns:
      The specified GameObject is returned; If the return value is null, meaning no GameObject exists at that position of that layer.

    • getGameObjectBy

      public GameObject getGameObjectBy​(int layer, java.awt.Point source, java.awt.Point delta)
      Gets the GameObject specified by the given position with a delta distance vector of the given layer.
      Parameters:
      layer - Integer specifying the layer index.
      source - Point object specifying the position of GameObject.
      delta - Point object specifying the delta vector to be translated.
      Returns:
      The specified GameObject is returned; If the return value is null, meaning no GameObject exists at that position of that layer.

    • refreshLevel

      public void refreshLevel()
      Generates/Resets the whole information of the current level:
      1. Tells DataManagerReset to reset the move count of player;
      2. Tells DataManagerReset to reset the timer;
      3. Resets and generates all layers of GameObjects by decoding raw level list of strings;
      See Also:
      DataManager.resetMoveCount(), DataManager.resetTime(), GamingScreenController.initialize(URL, ResourceBundle)

    • isLevelComplete

      public boolean isLevelComplete()
      Checks if the current level is completed by counting down all crates that hit diamonds.
      This method is called every time the PlayerController handling a valid user input.
      Returns:
      True is returned if all crates hit all diamonds; Otherwise, false is returned.
      See Also:
      PlayerController.handle(KeyEvent)

      Returns:
      A LevelIterator is returned to caller.
